00:40:13.240 --> 00:40:15.540
Recomienzo.

00:40:16.580 --> 00:40:19.260
Recomienzo.

00:40:19.260 --> 00:40:26.410
Reinicio este constante desplazarme
atravieso montañas desiertos y

00:40:26.410 --> 00:40:32.840
llanuras ni míos ni tuyos los
dominios de la imaginación.

00:40:32.840 --> 00:40:39.550
Ríos, volcanes, lavas y cenizas
un incendio interior me devora.

00:40:39.550 --> 00:40:44.320
Las sombras cabargan en la nueva
aurora peregrino por las cuatro

00:40:44.320 --> 00:40:50.120
estaciones derrumbo murallas
confundida entre la turba entre el

00:40:50.120 --> 00:40:51.940
huracán y las aves.

00:40:51.940 --> 00:40:53.950
Busco la antorcha.

00:40:53.950 --> 00:40:59.560
La palabra que dé en el blanco
el aroma de la hierba silvestre la

00:40:59.560 --> 00:41:06.280
patria de nostalgias y viborea en
mi cuerpo una violenta sensación

00:41:06.280 --> 00:41:07.580
de amor.

00:41:07.580 --> 00:41:08.880
&gt;&gt; Maureen Contreni: Again.

00:41:08.880 --> 00:41:15.640
It begins again, this
relentless journey over deserts

00:41:15.640 --> 00:41:22.190
and plains neither mine nor yours
but dominions of imagination.

00:41:22.190 --> 00:41:29.770
By lamplight I grope my way across
rivers, volcanoes, lava, and ash.

00:41:29.770 --> 00:41:32.650
A fire devours me from within.

00:41:32.650 --> 00:41:35.530
I return from the night
on the wings of sunrise,

00:41:35.530 --> 00:41:39.090 position:56%
a pilgrim crossing the four seasons.

00:41:39.090 --> 00:41:42.440
I demolish the ancient
walls of cities,

00:41:42.440 --> 00:41:47.840
confused in the teeming crowds
between the hurricane and the birds

00:41:47.840 --> 00:41:53.560
in search of a sliver of
light from a single word.

00:41:53.560 --> 00:41:58.050
Let the smell of wild grass,
the mother of nostalgia,

00:41:58.050 --> 00:42:02.120
strike at the heart of the
target and twist inside me

00:42:02.120 --> 00:42:05.170
with the violence of love.

00:42:05.170 --> 00:42:09.210
&gt;&gt; Consuelo Hernández: I have
to say that this book was written

00:42:09.210 --> 00:42:14.480
after I had experience of
suffer cancer and in front

00:42:14.480 --> 00:42:23.600
of one experience so hard, an
obstacle that's big to overcome,

00:42:23.600 --> 00:42:32.910
I come to value as never
life and also to find support

00:42:32.910 --> 00:42:39.200
in the highest inner self
or in whatever you believe

00:42:39.200 --> 00:42:42.110
that can help you in those moments.

00:42:42.110 --> 00:42:46.020
And I wrote this poem
too in those times.

00:42:46.020 --> 00:42:48.000
Tu nombre.

00:42:48.000 --> 00:42:51.480
Digo tu nombre y todos se ilumina.

00:42:51.480 --> 00:42:55.990
Pienso en tu nombre y
estoy lista para el viaje.

00:42:55.990 --> 00:43:00.030
Sueno tu nombre y me
despierto de una pesadilla.

00:43:00.030 --> 00:43:04.300
Escribo tu nombre y
aparece la palabra amor.

00:43:04.300 --> 00:43:09.490
Te llamo y brota agua en
el desierto de mi pena.

00:43:09.490 --> 00:43:17.580
Grito tu nombre y fecundas
de fulgor el universo.

00:43:17.580 --> 00:43:23.530
Me lleno de tu nombre y hay
esperanza limpia en mis caminos.

00:43:23.530 --> 00:43:31.660
Me abrazas, me besas y estoy viva.

00:43:31.660 --> 00:43:34.000
&gt;&gt; Maureen Contreni: Your name.

00:43:34.000 --> 00:43:37.820
I say your name and
everything lights up.

00:43:37.820 --> 00:43:42.120
I think about your name and
I am ready for a voyage.

00:43:42.120 --> 00:43:47.800
I dream your name and I
awake from a nightmare.

00:43:47.800 --> 00:43:51.260
I write your name and
the word love appears.

00:43:51.260 --> 00:43:55.620
I call to you and water sprouts
from the desert of my sorrow.

00:43:55.620 --> 00:44:00.750 position:56%
I shout your name and you impregnate
the universe with radiance.

00:44:00.750 --> 00:44:06.160
I fill myself with your name and
there is clean hope in my pathway.

00:44:06.160 --> 00:44:13.000
You hold me, you kiss
me, and I am alive.

00:44:13.000 --> 00:44:16.740
&gt;&gt; Consuelo Hernández: This
other poem is also something

00:44:16.740 --> 00:44:22.360
that I felt a necessity to
write when I was sick and it's

00:44:22.360 --> 00:44:25.310
to encourage people
to live even though

00:44:25.310 --> 00:44:30.340
if they are very depressed
or with a hard pain.

00:44:30.340 --> 00:44:34.710
I have had in my life friends
that have commit suicide,

00:44:34.710 --> 00:44:41.250
students that come to my
office with this immense pain,

00:44:42.450 --> 00:44:46.370
and at those moments
you realize that --

00:44:46.370 --> 00:44:48.520 position:56%
the moments when you are really sick

00:44:48.520 --> 00:44:52.140
and you realize how
much is important life

00:44:52.140 --> 00:44:58.890
and how much you value
life as the biggest present

00:44:58.890 --> 00:45:00.620
that we have in this world.

00:45:00.620 --> 00:45:06.060
So I wrote this poem to -- to
encourage people to value life

00:45:06.060 --> 00:45:11.400
and to forget those
ideas to commit suicide.

00:45:11.400 --> 00:45:15.340
Poema para suicidas.

00:45:15.340 --> 00:45:20.770 position:56%
Atrapa la llama que alumbra tus
orillas y posterga el descenso hacia

00:45:20.770 --> 00:45:26.790
el abismo aunque sientas que no hay
dolor más grande que el dolor de

00:45:26.790 --> 00:45:31.340
estar vivo ni mayor pesadumbre
que la vida consciente.

00:45:31.340 --> 00:45:37.670
Un veneno no sacia la
sed de firmamentos.

00:45:37.670 --> 00:45:44.190 position:56%
No prives de la brisa a tus pulmones
archiva navajas y cuchillos no

00:45:44.190 --> 00:45:47.520
visualices tu sangre a borbotones.

00:45:47.520 --> 00:45:50.870
Enciende las luminarias de tu alma.

00:45:50.870 --> 00:45:56.220 position:56%
Olvida las balas que marcaron
golondrinas con muertes imaginares y

00:45:56.220 --> 00:46:01.360
con el placer que bailas cumbia
o vallenato manda a la muerte a

00:46:01.360 --> 00:46:03.930
pudrirse en las letrinas.

00:46:03.930 --> 00:46:06.800
Antes de que emprendas tu regreso,

00:46:06.800 --> 00:46:14.690
descubre del cóndor su saber y
serena sin vértigo, sin asco,

00:46:14.690 --> 00:46:23.220
ante la carroña de los precipicios,
aprende a navegar en las alturas.

00:46:25.890 --> 00:46:29.210
&gt;&gt; Maureen Contreni:
For the suicidal.

00:46:29.210 --> 00:46:35.460 position:56%
Trap the flame that illuminates your
shores and hold back the dissent

00:46:35.460 --> 00:46:40.190
into the abyss even though you
feel there is no pain greater

00:46:40.190 --> 00:46:45.710
than the pain of being alive nor
grief heavier than conscious life.

00:46:45.710 --> 00:46:49.260
Poison does not quench
thirst for the heavens.

00:46:49.260 --> 00:46:51.960
Do not deprive your
lungs of the breeze.

00:46:51.960 --> 00:46:54.980
File away the razors and knives.

00:46:54.980 --> 00:46:58.790 position:56%
Do not visualize your blood gushing.

00:46:58.790 --> 00:47:00.710
Light the lamps of your soul.

00:47:00.710 --> 00:47:05.670
Forget the bullets that branded
the swallows with imaginary deaths.

00:47:05.670 --> 00:47:10.210
And with the pleasure with which
you danced the cumbia or vallenato,

00:47:10.210 --> 00:47:13.670
send Death to rot in the latrine.

00:47:13.670 --> 00:47:18.910
Before you set out on your
return, find the condor's wisdom

00:47:18.910 --> 00:47:24.820
and serenely, without vertigo or
disgust, faced with the carrion

00:47:24.820 --> 00:47:33.740
of the precipices, learn to
navigate in the highlands.

00:47:33.740 --> 00:47:36.890
&gt;&gt; Consuelo Hernández:
Casa de la infancia.

00:47:36.890 --> 00:47:42.200
Hoy volvé a rodar la lluvia entre
las tejas y salgo del cementerio

00:47:42.200 --> 00:47:44.100
mi abuelita.

00:47:44.100 --> 00:47:48.020
Se sentó como siempre
en alumbra de la cocina,

00:47:48.020 --> 00:47:51.710
con la mirada fijen
y ciertos a resuntas,

00:47:51.710 --> 00:47:58.030
y yo a tristezas por el cristo
fue que cantaba entre las ramas.

00:47:58.030 --> 00:48:01.540
Mi corazón se durmió
bajo las dalias.

00:48:01.540 --> 00:48:06.140
Mi ser senté rojo en todo
ese tiempo con las sales

00:48:06.140 --> 00:48:08.420
aurora luminosa.

00:48:08.420 --> 00:48:14.090
Siempre tengo que volverá la casa
de la infancia [inaudible] fugar en

00:48:14.090 --> 00:48:21.760
ese país [inaudible] por esos
caminos que no tienen piedad de

00:48:21.760 --> 00:48:24.500
las viajeras.

00:48:24.500 --> 00:48:26.540 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Maureen Contreni: Childhood home.

00:48:26.540 --> 00:48:29.750
Today the rain slipped
between the tiles

00:48:29.750 --> 00:48:32.900
and my grandmother hopped
out of the cemetery.

00:48:32.900 --> 00:48:37.550
She sat as usual on the
threshold of the kitchen

00:48:37.550 --> 00:48:42.000
with her gaze set on
uncertain horizons.

00:48:42.000 --> 00:48:47.490
And it rained sorrows for the great
cicadae sitting among the branches.

00:48:47.490 --> 00:48:50.400
My heart fell asleep
beneath the dahlias.

00:48:50.400 --> 00:48:54.260
My being was interred along
with that time, with the birds

00:48:54.260 --> 00:48:57.300
from some other luminous aurora.

00:48:58.480 --> 00:49:01.290
I always have to return
to my childhood home,

00:49:01.290 --> 00:49:06.060
to flounder in that deserted
country, on those destroyed paths

00:49:06.060 --> 00:49:08.240
that have no compassion
for travelers.

00:49:08.240 --> 00:49:12.810
&gt;&gt; Consuelo Hernández: And
now I'm going to read one poem

00:49:12.810 --> 00:49:17.030
that I think is more
actual than ever.

00:49:17.030 --> 00:49:21.320
It's La inmigrante
and it's devoted to --

00:49:21.320 --> 00:49:25.960
dedicated to all the
immigrant women.

00:49:27.940 --> 00:49:34.180 position:56%
Mujer que caminas noche y día con
tu llave inmemorial das nacimiento a

00:49:34.180 --> 00:49:42.080
la palabra veraz atraviesas el
río y nadie te reconoce, te mojas,

00:49:42.080 --> 00:49:45.350
sudas, pierdes tus zapatos.

00:49:45.350 --> 00:49:48.510
Otra jornada abrumada de cansancio,

00:49:48.510 --> 00:49:52.270
no puedes verbalizar tus
injurias pero eres sabia aunque te

00:49:52.270 --> 00:49:54.890
encuentren infraganti.

00:49:54.890 --> 00:49:56.570
Te interrogan.

00:49:56.570 --> 00:49:57.870
¿Quién eres?

00:49:57.870 --> 00:49:59.660
¿De dónde vienes?

00:49:59.660 --> 00:50:04.350
¿Qué buscas en esta tierra que ya
tiene dueños y fronteras y murallas

00:50:04.350 --> 00:50:08.230
y hermanos que saben
de la muerte lenta?

00:50:08.230 --> 00:50:16.020 position:56%
Al espacio de tu linaje vuelves como
sombra que releo en tu luminosa faz

00:50:16.020 --> 00:50:23.130
el fuego no termina escapas,
caes, te levantas, te sacudes,

00:50:23.130 --> 00:50:28.800
hablas en tu lengua de tortilla
muerdes tus palabras de café y no

00:50:28.800 --> 00:50:32.080
te dejas derrotar por la nostalgia.

00:50:32.080 --> 00:50:39.660 position:56%
Tu canto se ahoga, se alejan las
salidas eres inmigrante tu identidad

00:50:39.660 --> 00:50:42.630
se ha reducido para siempre.

00:50:42.630 --> 00:50:49.070 position:56%
No entiendes de visas ni de planetas
fragmentados aprendes a decir

00:50:49.070 --> 00:50:52.070
"good morning" pero
a nadie le interesa

00:50:52.070 --> 00:50:57.730 position:56%
"how you are" ni que estés habitada
por un hijo sepultado en el desierto

00:50:57.730 --> 00:51:03.990
por el sueño de un empleo de
un refugio para dormir en paz.

00:51:03.990 --> 00:51:09.470
Yo también soy la ruptura de la
costura aquí adentro no se disipa

00:51:09.470 --> 00:51:19.730
la niebla, y me sucede que
miro en tu espejo y me veo.

00:51:19.730 --> 00:51:22.580
&gt;&gt; Maureen Contreni:
Immigrant woman.

00:51:22.580 --> 00:51:27.510
Woman that walks night and day
with your memor -- in memorial key.

00:51:27.510 --> 00:51:30.660
You give rise to the true word.

00:51:30.660 --> 00:51:34.460
You cross the river and
no one acknowledges you.

00:51:34.460 --> 00:51:39.650
You get wet, you sweat,
you lose your shoes.

00:51:39.650 --> 00:51:43.520
Another day's journey
burdened with exhaustion.

00:51:43.520 --> 00:51:47.590
You cannot verbalize your
injuries, but you are wise even

00:51:47.590 --> 00:51:49.980
if they catch you red-handed.

00:51:49.980 --> 00:51:51.340
They interrogate you.

00:51:51.340 --> 00:51:52.640
Who are you?

00:51:52.640 --> 00:51:54.100
Where are you from?

00:51:54.100 --> 00:51:58.130 position:56%
What do you want from this land that
already has owners, and borders,

00:51:58.130 --> 00:52:02.940
and walls, and brothers
who know about slow death.

00:52:02.940 --> 00:52:05.830
To the place of your lineage
you return like a shadow

00:52:05.830 --> 00:52:09.710
that I reread in your
luminous visage.

00:52:09.710 --> 00:52:11.170
The fire does not end.

00:52:11.170 --> 00:52:14.370
You escape, you fall, you get up.

00:52:14.370 --> 00:52:16.200
You shake yourself off.

00:52:16.200 --> 00:52:21.220
You speak in your tortilla
tongue coffee words.

00:52:21.220 --> 00:52:25.260
Do not let nostalgia defeat you.

00:52:25.260 --> 00:52:26.890
Your song drowns.

00:52:26.890 --> 00:52:29.500
The exits get farther away.

00:52:29.500 --> 00:52:31.150
You are in immigrant.

00:52:31.150 --> 00:52:35.410
Your identity has been
reduced forever.

00:52:35.410 --> 00:52:40.590
You neither understand about
visas nor fragmented planets.

00:52:40.590 --> 00:52:46.000 position:56%
You learn to say good morning, but
no one is interested in how you are,

00:52:46.000 --> 00:52:51.640
or that you are inhabited by a
son buried in the desert by hope

00:52:51.640 --> 00:52:56.730
of getting a job, of a
refuge to sleep in peace.

00:52:56.730 --> 00:53:00.440
I too am the rupture and the scene.

00:53:00.440 --> 00:53:05.430
Here inside the fog does not
dissipate and so it happens

00:53:05.430 --> 00:53:11.350
that I look at your reflection
in the mirror and I see myself.

00:53:13.230 --> 00:53:16.000
&gt;&gt; Consuelo Hernández:
Volver a la niñez.

00:53:16.000 --> 00:53:21.230
Volver a la niñez, se dice
fácil, al delantal de flores,

00:53:21.230 --> 00:53:26.180
al mate rile-rile-ró, al tuntún
del diablo con el tridente al

00:53:26.180 --> 00:53:29.430
hombro, al ángel con
el bastón dorado,

00:53:29.430 --> 00:53:33.270
a las madrugadas de
cuatro de la mañana,

00:53:33.270 --> 00:53:37.110
a visitar los templos
con devoción forzada.

00:53:37.110 --> 00:53:39.360
Volver a los juegos de pelota,

00:53:39.360 --> 00:53:44.450
a escalar los montes de los
Andes con frío avaricioso,

00:53:44.450 --> 00:53:48.500
cruzar el puente sobre el
ruido infernal de la quebrada,

00:53:48.500 --> 00:53:51.710 position:56%
con un miedo que muerde las agallas.

00:53:51.710 --> 00:53:56.920
En verdad poco hay de
memorable en todo esto,

00:53:56.920 --> 00:53:59.270
tal vez mi soledad entre la hierba,

00:53:59.270 --> 00:54:03.030
el diálogo inconcluso
con los pájaros,

00:54:03.030 --> 00:54:07.660 position:56%
y mi permanente envidia de sus alas.

00:54:07.660 --> 00:54:12.130
Mas para qué toda esta
perorata de nostalgias,

00:54:12.130 --> 00:54:18.360 position:56%
si al final sé que soy igual que
el Amazonas o el Potomac que siempre

00:54:18.360 --> 00:54:23.460
van y nunca pueden volver
a su punto de partida.

00:54:23.460 --> 00:54:28.630
&gt;&gt; Maureen Contreni:
Back to childhood.

00:54:29.840 --> 00:54:35.270
Back to childhood, it's easily
said, to the flowery apron,

00:54:35.270 --> 00:54:40.120
to mate rile-rile-ró, to the
beat of the devil with a pitchfork

00:54:40.120 --> 00:54:43.820
on his shoulder, to the
angel with the golden staff,

00:54:43.820 --> 00:54:46.730
to the early starts
at 4 in the morning,

00:54:46.730 --> 00:54:49.930
visiting temples with
forced devotion.

00:54:50.970 --> 00:54:54.270
Back to ball games, to
climbing the Andes mountains

00:54:54.270 --> 00:54:59.330
in the grasping cold, to crossing
the bridge over the inferno noise

00:54:59.330 --> 00:55:04.000
of the gorge, with fear
gnawing at our insides.

00:55:04.000 --> 00:55:07.390
Honestly, little of
this is memorable.

00:55:07.390 --> 00:55:12.640
Perhaps just my loneliness in the
grass, my inconclusive dialogue

00:55:12.640 --> 00:55:18.080
with the birds, and my
permanent envy of their wings.

00:55:18.080 --> 00:55:20.850
But why all this nostalgic
sing-songing

00:55:20.850 --> 00:55:25.990
if in the end I know I'm just
like the Amazon o r the Potomac

00:55:25.990 --> 00:55:31.370
that always flow and never
return to their starting point.

00:55:31.370 --> 00:55:34.240
&gt;&gt; Consuelo Hernández:
And I'm going to conclude

00:55:34.240 --> 00:55:37.260
with this poem for my parents.

00:55:37.260 --> 00:55:42.600
I am also an orphan already
and this is already sad poem,

00:55:42.600 --> 00:55:45.070
but I want to read it here.

00:55:45.070 --> 00:55:46.370
Te fuiste.

00:55:46.370 --> 00:55:51.780
Te fuiste a mitad de
la cosecha de verano,

00:55:51.780 --> 00:55:55.420
entraste a casa del silencio.

00:55:55.420 --> 00:55:58.260
Todas las palabras recogiste.

00:55:58.260 --> 00:56:04.390
No dejaste con la mirada húmeda y
el corazón luchando contra pelo.

00:56:04.390 --> 00:56:10.490
Que triste aquella noche contigo
hasta alba sin oírte pronunciar

00:56:10.490 --> 00:56:12.500
una palabra.

00:56:12.500 --> 00:56:18.980 position:56%
Te miraba y desde la eternidad de mi
sonreías con tus ojos cerrados de

00:56:18.980 --> 00:56:24.170
ternura y tu andar
detenido por siempre.

00:56:24.170 --> 00:56:27.740
Repetí tu nombre hasta
el cansancio.

00:56:27.740 --> 00:56:34.360 position:56%
Los momentos que pasamos conversando
y te vivirte como estatua en mi

00:56:34.360 --> 00:56:37.620
misma me habitadas.

00:56:37.620 --> 00:56:44.530
Hoy en el reino del insomnios estás
aquí suavizando mi dolor con tu

00:56:44.530 --> 00:56:49.520
pecho generoso y tus
últimas palabras:

00:56:49.520 --> 00:56:51.970
Hija mía que Dios me la bendiga.

00:56:56.580 --> 00:56:58.400
&gt;&gt; Maureen Contreni: You went away.

00:56:58.400 --> 00:57:02.360
You went away in the middle
of the summer harvest.

00:57:02.360 --> 00:57:04.600
You entered the house of silence.

00:57:04.600 --> 00:57:07.400
You gathered up all your words.

00:57:07.400 --> 00:57:09.610
With a damp look, you left us

00:57:09.610 --> 00:57:13.870
with our hearts struggling
against the tide.

00:57:13.870 --> 00:57:16.570
Such an unhappy night
with you until dawn,

00:57:16.570 --> 00:57:19.640
not hearing you utter one word.

00:57:19.640 --> 00:57:24.430
I looked at you and you smiled
back at me from eternity.

00:57:24.430 --> 00:57:26.580
With your closed eyes
and tenderness,

00:57:26.580 --> 00:57:29.940
your movement stopped forever.

00:57:29.940 --> 00:57:34.400
I repeated your name to exhaustion,
the times we spent talking.

00:57:34.400 --> 00:57:38.500
I saw you rise up like
a statue inside me.

00:57:38.500 --> 00:57:40.520
You inhabited me.

00:57:40.520 --> 00:57:46.110
Today in the kingdom of insomnia
you are here softening my pain,

00:57:46.110 --> 00:57:50.510
with your generous chest,
and your last words:

00:57:50.510 --> 00:57:55.510
God bless you, my daughter.

00:57:55.510 --> 00:58:05.790
[ Applause ]

00:58:05.790 --> 00:58:07.210
&gt;&gt; Catalina Gómez:
That was just beautiful.

00:58:07.210 --> 00:58:08.510
Thank you both.

00:58:08.510 --> 00:58:11.250
And just a small reminder that
we're selling Consuelo's book here

00:58:11.250 --> 00:58:12.550
in the back.

00:58:12.550 --> 00:58:14.070
Thank you for coming.

00:58:14.070 --> 00:58:15.370
Thanks.

